#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn3.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 1. Paṭhamavagga → bandhanavaggo (bj) | bandhanavaggo paṭhamo (pts2)
msgctxt "sn3.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. Shackles "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn3.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Daharasutta "
msgstr "1. Young "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts1ed1.68, pts2ed1.157, sc1
msgctxt "sn3.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn3.1:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.1:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then King Pasenadi of Kosala went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "sn3.1:1.4"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn3.1:1.5"
msgid "“bhavampi no gotamo anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddhoti paṭijānātī”ti? "
msgstr "“Does Master Gotama claim to have awakened to the supreme perfect awakening?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: mameva → mamaṃ (bj, pts2) | maman (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn3.1:1.6"
msgid "“Yañhi taṃ, mahārāja, sammā vadamāno vadeyya ‘anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti, mameva taṃ sammā vadamāno vadeyya. "
msgstr "“If anyone should rightly be said to have awakened to the supreme perfect awakening, it’s me. "

msgctxt "sn3.1:1.7"
msgid "Ahañhi, mahārāja, anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho”ti. "
msgstr "For, great king, I have awakened to the supreme perfect awakening.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.158, sc2
msgctxt "sn3.1:2.1"
msgid "“Yepi te, bho gotama, samaṇabrāhmaṇā saṅghino gaṇino gaṇācariyā ñātā yasassino titthakarā sādhusammatā bahujanassa, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "“Well, there are those ascetics and brahmins who lead an order and a community, and teach a community. They’re well-known and famous religious founders, regarded as holy by many people. That is, "

msgctxt "sn3.1:2.2"
msgid "pūraṇo kassapo, makkhali gosālo, nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto, sañcayo belaṭṭhaputto, pakudho kaccāyano, ajito kesakambalo; "
msgstr "Pūraṇa Kassapa, Makkhali Gosāla, Nigaṇṭha Nāṭaputta, Sañjaya Belaṭṭhiputta, Pakudha Kaccāyana, and Ajita Kesakambala. "

msgctxt "sn3.1:2.3"
msgid "tepi mayā ‘anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddhoti paṭijānāthā’ti puṭṭhā samānā anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddhoti na paṭijānanti. "
msgstr "I also asked them whether they claimed to have awakened to the supreme perfect awakening, but they made no such claim. "

msgctxt "sn3.1:2.4"
msgid "Kiṃ pana bhavaṃ gotamo daharo ceva jātiyā navo ca pabbajjāyā”ti? "
msgstr "So why do you, given that you’re so young in age and newly gone forth?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.69, pts2ed1.159, sc3
msgctxt "sn3.1:3.1"
msgid "“Cattāro kho me, mahārāja, daharāti na uññātabbā, daharāti na paribhotabbā. "
msgstr "“Great king, these four things should not be looked down on or disparaged because they are young. "

msgctxt "sn3.1:3.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn3.1:3.3"
msgid "Khattiyo kho, mahārāja, daharoti na uññātabbo, daharoti na paribhotabbo. "
msgstr "An aristocrat, "

msgctxt "sn3.1:3.4"
msgid "Urago kho, mahārāja, daharoti na uññātabbo, daharoti na paribhotabbo. "
msgstr "a snake, "

msgctxt "sn3.1:3.5"
msgid "Aggi kho, mahārāja, daharoti na uññātabbo, daharoti na paribhotabbo. "
msgstr "a fire, "

msgctxt "sn3.1:3.6"
msgid "Bhikkhu, kho, mahārāja, daharoti na uññātabbo, daharoti na paribhotabbo. "
msgstr "and a mendicant. "

msgctxt "sn3.1:3.7"
msgid "Ime kho, mahārāja, cattāro daharāti na uññātabbā, daharāti na paribhotabbā”ti. "
msgstr "These four things should not be looked down on or disparaged because they are young.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn3.1:4.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "sn3.1:4.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā: "
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn3.1:5.1"
msgid "“Khattiyaṃ jātisampannaṃ, "
msgstr "“A man should not despise "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:5.2"
msgid "abhijātaṃ yasassinaṃ; "
msgstr "an aristocrat of impeccable lineage, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:5.3"
msgid "Daharoti nāvajāneyya, "
msgstr "high-born and famous, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:5.4"
msgid "na naṃ paribhave naro. "
msgstr "just because they’re young. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn3.1:6.1"
msgid "Ṭhānañhi so manujindo, "
msgstr "For it’s possible that that lord of men, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:6.2"
msgid "rajjaṃ laddhāna khattiyo; "
msgstr "as aristocrat, will gain the throne. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:6.3"
msgid "So kuddho rājadaṇḍena, "
msgstr "And in his anger he’ll execute a royal punishment, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:6.4"
msgid "tasmiṃ pakkamate bhusaṃ; "
msgstr "and have you violently beaten. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:6.5"
msgid "Tasmā taṃ parivajjeyya, "
msgstr "Hence you should avoid him "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:6.6"
msgid "rakkhaṃ jīvitamattano. "
msgstr "for the sake of your own life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn3.1:7.1"
msgid "Gāme vā yadi vā raññe, "
msgstr "Whether in village or wilderness, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:7.2"
msgid "yattha passe bhujaṅgamaṃ; "
msgstr "wherever a serpent is seen, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:7.3"
msgid "Daharoti nāvajāneyya, "
msgstr "a man should not look down on it "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:7.4"
msgid "na naṃ paribhave naro. "
msgstr "or despise it for its youth. "

# NOTE: Compare the devas of SN 2.29
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.160, sc8
msgctxt "sn3.1:8.1"
msgid "Uccāvacehi vaṇṇehi, "
msgstr "With its rainbow of colors, "

# NOTE: BB has “fierce” for tejasi, which misses the point. It’s an allusion to the venomous bite, teja having roots in both “sharp” and “fiery”. This metaphor is the origin of the dragon’s fiery breath.
#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: tejasī → tejasā (si) | tejasi (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn3.1:8.2"
msgid "urago carati tejasī; "
msgstr "the snake of fiery breath glides along. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:8.3"
msgid "So āsajja ḍaṃse bālaṃ, "
msgstr "It lashes out and bites the fool, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:8.4"
msgid "naraṃ nāriñca ekadā; "
msgstr "both men and women alike. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:8.5"
msgid "Tasmā taṃ parivajjeyya, "
msgstr "Hence you should avoid it "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:8.6"
msgid "rakkhaṃ jīvitamattano. "
msgstr "for the sake of your own life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn3.1:9.1"
msgid "Pahūtabhakkhaṃ jālinaṃ, "
msgstr "A fire devours a huge amount, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:9.2"
msgid "pāvakaṃ kaṇhavattaniṃ; "
msgstr "a conflagration with a blackened trail. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:9.3"
msgid "Daharoti nāvajāneyya, "
msgstr "A man should not look down on it "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:9.4"
msgid "na naṃ paribhave naro. "
msgstr "just because it’s young. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn3.1:10.1"
msgid "Laddhā hi so upādānaṃ, "
msgstr "For once it gets fuel "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:10.2"
msgid "mahā hutvāna pāvako; "
msgstr "it’ll become a huge conflagration. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: ḍahe → ḍase (bj) | dahe (pts2, mr)
msgctxt "sn3.1:10.3"
msgid "So āsajja ḍahe bālaṃ, "
msgstr "It’ll lash out and burn the fool, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:10.4"
msgid "naraṃ nāriñca ekadā; "
msgstr "both men and women alike. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:10.5"
msgid "Tasmā taṃ parivajjeyya, "
msgstr "Hence you should avoid it "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:10.6"
msgid "rakkhaṃ jīvitamattano. "
msgstr "for the sake of your own life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
#. VAR: ḍahati → dahati (mr)
msgctxt "sn3.1:11.1"
msgid "Vanaṃ yadaggi ḍahati, "
msgstr "When a forest is burned by fire, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:11.2"
msgid "pāvako kaṇhavattanī; "
msgstr "a conflagration with a blackened trail, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:11.3"
msgid "Jāyanti tattha pārohā, "
msgstr "the shoots will spring up there again, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:11.4"
msgid "ahorattānamaccaye. "
msgstr "with the passing of the days and nights. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.161, sc12
msgctxt "sn3.1:12.1"
msgid "Yañca kho sīlasampanno, "
msgstr "But if a mendicant endowed with ethics "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:12.2"
msgid "bhikkhu ḍahati tejasā; "
msgstr "burns you with their power, "

# NOTE: PTS dict gives this ref for pasu = cattle and pasava = offspring.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:12.3"
msgid "Na tassa puttā pasavo, "
msgstr "you’ll have no sons or cattle, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:12.4"
msgid "dāyādā vindare dhanaṃ; "
msgstr "nor will your heirs find wealth. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:12.5"
msgid "Anapaccā adāyādā, "
msgstr "Childless and heirless you become, "

# NOTE: BB gives the doctrinally correct Buddhist explanation for this. But as it stands, the text reads as if the mendicant is exacting fiery vengeance with their psychic power.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:12.6"
msgid "tālāvatthū bhavanti te. "
msgstr "like a palm-tree stump. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.70, sc13
msgctxt "sn3.1:13.1"
msgid "Tasmā hi paṇḍito poso, "
msgstr "That’s why an astute person, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:13.2"
msgid "sampassaṃ atthamattano; "
msgstr "seeing what’s good for themselves, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:13.3"
msgid "Bhujaṅgamaṃ pāvakañca, "
msgstr "would always treat these properly: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:13.4"
msgid "khattiyañca yasassinaṃ; "
msgstr "a snake, a conflagration, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:13.5"
msgid "Bhikkhuñca sīlasampannaṃ, "
msgstr "a famous aristocrat, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.1:13.6"
msgid "sammadeva samācare”ti. "
msgstr "and a mendicant endowed with ethics.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn3.1:14.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When this was said, King Pasenadi of Kosala said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn3.1:14.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“Excellent, sir! Excellent! "

#. VAR: nikkujjitaṃ → nikujjitaṃ (?)
msgctxt "sn3.1:14.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito. "
msgstr "As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "sn3.1:14.4"
msgid "Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca. "
msgstr "I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "sn3.1:14.5"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”"

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
